Creaming index represents the emulsion stability against phase separation due to the creaming phenomenon. The centrifugal instability method was applied to determine the creaming index of samples. Emulsions (25 mL) were centrifuged at 2800 g for 15 min at 25 °C. The magnitude of the creaming phenomenon was determined after centrifugation by measuring the height of the cream upper layer (HC) and the height of the total emulsion (HT) in centimeters. Creaming index was then calculated using the following formula:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
