For total isoflavones content determination (TI), 10 mg of sample was dispersed in 50 mL of 96% ethanol. The dispersion was sonicated at the amplitude of ultrasound probe of 75 kHz, at 45 ºC for 20 min, then filtered through a glass filter. An aliquot from the filtrate was separated into 2 parts, one was mixed with 0.025 M potassium chloride buffer at pH 1.0 and another part of the filtrate was mixed with 0.4 M sodium acetate buffer at pH 4.5 to obtain the final volume of 10 mL for each pH value. Isoflavones were spectrophotometrically measured for absorbance at 262 and 660 nm. Whereby, 660 nm was absorbance for turbidity correction of a sample. Isoflavones content was calculated as a function of genistein using the following equation:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
