The antioxidant activity of samples was evaluated using 2,2-diphenyl-1-picryl-hydrazyl (DPPH) assay. A methanolic solution of DPPH radicals (10− 4 mol/L) was freshly prepared before each experiment. Approximately, 40 mg of sample was transferred to a 10 mL volumetric flask and 1 mL of DPPH solution was added. The mixture was vortexed and kept in the dark for 30 min. The control solution was prepared by mixing 1 mL of DPPH solution with 6 mL of methanol. The absorbance was measured using a spectrophotometry at a wavelength of 515 nm. The free radical scavenger activity was calculated as the following equation.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
